div.p:
The panels included some Americans such as Betty Friedan of the National Women’s Political Caucus;
                            Ruth Clusen of the League of Women Voters and a member of the U.S.
                            Delegation; Luke Lee from the Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy;
                            Madonna Gilbert of the Rapid City American Indian Movement; Florence
                            Jackson of the Bureau of Social Studies, New York Board of Education;
                            Mary Ann Krupsak, Lieutenant Governor of New York. Nira Long of AID was
                            to have been on a panels but when assignments at the governmental
                            Conference conflicted, her place was very ably taken by Nan Frederick of
                            AID.
